Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Halve, peel, and mince @shallot{1}(halved, peeled, and minced). Mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}(minced or grated). Strip @rosemary{1/4%ounce}(stripped from stems) from stems and discard stems. Finely chop leaves until you have 2 tsp. Finely chop @sun-dried tomatoes{3%ounce}. Trim any tough ends from @green beans{12%ounce}(trimmed).

Soak @white bread{2%slices} with @chicken stock concentrate{2} and 1/4 cup water in #medium bowl{}. Break up with your hands until pasty. Add @ground beef{20%ounce}, sun-dried tomatoes, shallot, half the garlic, half the rosemary, and a large pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Mix with your hands until just combined. Form into four oval loaves and place on a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}. Bake in oven until cooked through, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, peel and dice @russet potato{24%ounce}(peeled and diced) into 1/2-inch cubes. Place potatoes and a large pinch of @salt{pinch} in a #medium pot{}. Add enough water to cover by 1 inch, then bring to a boil. Reduce to a simmer and cook until potatoes are tender, about ~{12%minutes}.

Toss green beans with a large drizzle of @extra virgin olive oil{3%teaspoon} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch} on another baking sheet. Roast in oven until green beans are tender, about ~{15%minutes}.

Once tender, drain potatoes. In same pot used for potatoes, heat @butter{2%tablespoon}, remaining garlic, and remaining chopped rosemary over medium heat. Melt and cook until fragrant, about ~{30%seconds}. Add potatoes and 1/4 cup @milk{1/4%cup} and mash with a #fork{} or #potato masher{} until very smooth. Season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

Divide mashed potatoes between plates. Top each with green beans and a meatloaf and serve.